        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Stage1 Subjects were included in the condition of adults with good health and no
             mobility disorder. They will be considered by healthy young people over the age of 20.

        It is estimated that 12 males and 12 females will be called.

          -  Stage2 Forty patients with a stroke of more than six months have been admitted.

        Subjects were included as follows:

          1. stroke for more than 6 months;

          2. current stable condition;

          3. able to walk independently for more than 5 meters, and if necessary, use auxiliary
             equipment;

          4. before and after the two feet Stand in a straight line for more than 10 seconds;

          5. can understand spoken instructions.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Stage1

               1. unable to stand with the feet and the walker;

               2. pregnant;

               3. within six months will affect the walking or standing surgery (such as limbs,
                  spine or brain surgery);

               4. other Physical and mental state is not suitable.

          -  Stage2

               1. unable to stand and walk with both feet;

               2. suffering from diabetes or other diseases combined with peripheral neuropathy,
                  causing a poor sense of body or a neurological disease affecting lower limb
                  movement and sensory function;

               3. suffering from hemophilia Patients with diseases, other blood-related diseases or
                  severe peripheral vascular diseases;

               4. those who are pregnant;

               5. those who have been affected by walking or standing within six months (such as
                  limb, spine or brain surgery);

               6. Other physical and mental states are not suitable.
